How diverse can nature be?

For high-res images: Type a resolution multiplier number on live view. If you type 2, it will render 2 times larger than your screen size. Press "s" to save.

metadata.name: Stitched: Trauma #44
metadata.description:
"Every happy family is alike; every unhappy family is unhappy in its own way." -- Tolstoy

Stitched: trauma is based on the same code, and premise, as Stitched, with one twist: childhood trauma distorts experiences and events; some are wildly chaotic; others obsessively retrace a few curves. It is an experiment in combinatorial complexity: are two mints ever indistinguishable? 

The distortion has been carefully designed to allow a huge space of legibly distinct possibilities.

controls:

mouse click or space bar: pause / unpause / reset animation
s: save current frame
f: toggle between square format and stretch aspect ratio
1-6: set pixel density

attributes.name: Symmetry
attributes.value: Reflection in y, Reflection in x, Reflection across x+y=0

metadata.name: Vorticity #15
metadata.description:
Vorticity is a gpu-accelerated flow field. The particles in the flow field orbit around a set of points that move around over time.

Controls: Click and drag to push particles away. Press the space bar to pause the simulation, and again to resume. While paused, you can press "n" to advance the simulation a single step. Press "r" to restart the simulation (if you change the resolution of the screen after the page loads, you will need to restart to update the resolution).

metadata.name: Rings #30
metadata.description:
Rings is the cummulative texturized generative artwork obtained after several animations of a determinated number of particles seeking a concentric pattern in several rings. But in this case, to get some different results of depth and texture, the chosen particles weregeometrical 2D shapes (like lines, circles, squares and triangles). Also, white 1D dots with low stroke in a descentralized radius from pattern center brings a nice highlighting effect, helping the depth feeling.
All the codes were developed and studyed for a quite time, and after a high number of tests and modifications I believe Rings is ready to be yours!

Its a big pleasure be back :)

And again....palletes carefully chosen.

See the features! Ranking system set up!

Press 's' to save canvas.
Nice experience at full view.

metadata.name: tied #33
metadata.description:
"tied" is trying to represent the feeling of pressure over people.
To represent that I did an abstraction with points trapped by lines and dense textures, some of these points is stucked in the middle of the road, trying to get out of the background to reach surface.


this is my last contribution to fx beta.

a project made with p5.js and love to make part of it.


Omar Lobato Neto, 19/03/2022

metadata.name: Suspension #35
metadata.description:
Suspension uses simple objects to create structures suspended in space, held together by relation and composition.

The unique composition algorithm is random enough to produce infinite variations, but ordered enough to produce engaging artworks that are instantly recognizable.

Suspension uses negative space, additive coloring, and a unique rendering technique to create a very distinct style. 

It has many hand tuned palettes, with rare palettes that produce incisive variations.

Suspension is responsive and will render fast at any resolution. It looks great on wide screens of 2K, 4K or larger.

To accommodate the variation in displays, you can use the up/down arrow keys to adjust the brightness. 'r' resets to the default values.

's' will save an image in the exact size of the window, so you can create images in any resolution.
